description:
This restaurant is fantastic and I will definitely be back.  

We came here on a Saturday night just after 9pm and there was no wait for a party of two.  Everything on the menu sounded so good it was difficult to decide what to order.  Thankfully the server provided some helpful recommendations.  We ordered: 

- Roasted Beets with Labneh, Dill, Pomegranate Molasses & Pickled Onion; 
- Mozzarella di Bufala with Mixed Herb Pesto, Crème Fraîche & Toasted Focaccia;
-Tomato Braised Pork Meatballs with Creamy Polenta & Reggiano; 
- Chicken Cacciatore special 

The portions were generous and this was more than enough food for two people.  Everything was delicious - in particular I enjoyed the buffalo mozzarella.  It was super creamy and I loved that it came with toast and ample amounts of pesto.  The meatballs were also very good; I would definitely order these again.  I also enjoyed the chicken dish, however it was quite salty (and I say this as a person who loves salt).  

We stayed past their closing time yet they were extremely nice and did not rush us out.  The restaurant has a pleasant atmosphere - not too loud or bright and the tables are spaced a good distance from each other.  This would be a great place to come with a group so that you can try a lot of different dishes.  

Definitely recommend coming here if you like Mediterranean food.

loved the space/ambiance. neat lines, modern, a bit of brick. casual sleek. 

Sunday nite wine specials= yay. had the cuvee reserve rouge from lebanon that was very unique and yum. 

shared:

eggplant w/ feta, chilies, pomegranate molasses & mint
//very tasty but a bit  a too saucy for my taste//

chaterelle mushrooms w/ marsala, creme fraiche, thyme over crispy polenta
//love polenta, love mushrooms, very yum//

free range chicken speidini w/ bread, cilantro, chile & onions
//kinda reminded me of zuni roast chicken w/ bread salad, tender chicken and yum bread pieces, i liked the concept//

grilled niman ranch skirt steak w/heirloom potatoes, mixed greens  & chimichurri: cooked to medium rare
//steak was tender and flavorful but seemed to be cooked unevenly.. tasty but not my favorite dish//

warm apple crisp w/ vanilla ice cream
//liked the cinamon and pecans very autumn-appropriate//

service was great.

overall would go back. the only other mediterranean place i like in sf is kokkari. also delicious but different ambiance.
